Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: 1:58 PM Defendant Danielle Christean Murray in court.  Attorney Kelly James Mattingly in court for Danielle Christean Murray.  Prosecuting attorney Margaret Nan Ginocchio in court for the State of Wisconsin. Felony hold open agreement filed, court accepts the hold open agreement. Defendant pleads guilty to count two. Court withholds findings of guilt pending hold open agreement.  Defendant pleads no contest to count one, court finds the defendant guilty. Court orders sentence withheld, 18 months probation with conditions, Complete any assessment/treatment/counseling deemed necessary, Court Costs due December 9 2022. Felony rights given to defendant. If defendant successfully completes all conditions of hold open agreement, defendant may petition to dismiss count two only, and petition for expungement on Count one. Bond continues on count two. 2 Days Credit.
